        {"body":"ODETTA doesn't recommend having New Year's Eve for a birthday. The deeply inspirational folk and blues singer, who will perform a cappella at the \"New Year's Eve Concert for Peace\" tonight at the Cathedral of St. John the Divine, was born 66 years ago today. And in her opinion, it was a total rip-off. \"We were a poor family in Los Angeles,\" she", "byline":"By BOB MORRIS", "date":"19951231", "title":"No More New Year-Birthday Blues", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/style/no-more-new-year-birthday-blues.html"},
        {"body":"An American soldier was wounded when his vehicle hit a land mine in northeastern Bosnia today, becoming the first American casualty of the NATO-led peacekeeping mission, military officials said. The soldier, Spec. Martin John Begosh of Rockville, Md., was injured when an anti-tank land mine exploded beneath a vehicle carrying military police", "byline":"By IAN FISHER", "date":"19951231", "title":"Land Mine Wounds Soldier, the First U.S. Casualty in Bosnia", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/world/land-mine-wounds-soldier-the-first-us-casualty-in-bosnia.html"},
        {"body":"Twenty years after his death, Emperor Haile Selassie still does not have an official resting place. His coffin lies in the crypt of the Bhata Church, an Ethiopian Orthodox church here, next to the marble tomb of his great-uncle, Emperor Menelik II. It is behind glass in what appears to be the crypt's closet, draped in maroon, gold-brocaded velvet,", "byline":"By DONATELLA LORCH", "date":"19951231", "title":"Ethiopia Deals With Legacy of Kings and Colonels", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/world/ethiopia-deals-with-legacy-of-kings-and-colonels.html"},
        {"body":"MOVING is seldom easy, but changing addresses can become a nightmare when a moving company presents a bill that is miles off its own estimate or when some possessions fail to turn up at the end of the trip. About 16.5 million households move every year, with 1 million of those across state lines. Few of them realize at the outset just how much", "byline":"By ANDREA ADELSON", "date":"19951231", "title":"SPENDING IT;Boxing Up a Life and Moving It Requires Caution and Cash", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/business/spending-it-boxing-up-a-life-and-moving-it-requires-caution-and-cash.html"},
        {"body":"Shanghai is the New York of China. Its pace of life is palpably faster, its sense of style more flamboyant, and its inhabitants' opinion of themselves noticeably higher than anywhere else in the nation. Chinese from smaller cities sometimes fear Shanghai's fast-talking and quick-changing ways, but for those who like big-city life, Shanghai is the", "byline":"By SETH FAISON", "date":"19951231", "title":"WHAT'S DOING IN;Shanghai", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/travel/what-s-doing-in-shanghai.html"},
        {"body":"The \"little salon\" is a refuge of counter stools and ungainly chairs in the cluttered rear of the Tabagie Grand-pere, a tobacco, coffee and news shop on Boulevard St. Laurent, where everyone meets. Until recently, the arguments were so heated in Louiseville's version of a country store on Main Street U.S.A. that the Tabagie's owner, Michel", "byline":"By CLYDE H. FARNSWORTH", "date":"19951231", "title":"Small Town In Quebec Just Awaits Next Vote", "url":"http://www.nytimes.com/1995/12/31/world/small-town-in-quebec-just-awaits-next-vote.html"}
